description: This 1965 Dodge Coronet has the right combination of originality, upgrades, and attitude that makes mid-60s Mopars so special. From the handsome styling, to the unique interior, to the 383 V8, this neat hardtop is a seldom-seen Dodge that delivers performance and big car comfort in one sleek package.

The Dark Turquoise Metallic seen here is a professional respray of a 1965-correct color.  So you get the benefit of looking right for the era, but now with a standout shine.  Its luster is perfect for highlighting Chrysler's famous cantilever styling. Plus, there's added attraction that comes from the well-defined panels.  The doors open and close with authority, and everything lines up rather well. Just as crucial to highlighting this Mopar is the brightwork, which is all present and quite nice. It helps feature the extra-wide front end, angular hardtop, and runs the full length of this coupe.  It all has a very period-correct style, except for those large 17-inch Rocket Racing alloys.  They don't look out of place on this classic, but they certainly hint at some extra power.

The interior is a high-quality presentation two-tone where the darker elements on the seats seem to match nicely with the exterior color.  The brighter turquoise that dominates the rest of the interior has a level of freshness that tells you there was more investment here.  The factory steering wheel and the big bright dash panel are Mopar works of art.   And while this is all factory-correct, the trio of auxiliary gauges are another hint there's something special under the hood.

This was at the dawn of the muscle car era, and this one celebrates it correctly.  1965 was the first year the 383 cubic-inch big block V8 was offered in the Coronet, and so we're happy to see a 1960s block in this coupe.  It's presented nicely with the painted inner fenders, tidy wire setup, and Mopar valve covers & air topper.  And when you look beyond the style, this one also has the performance substance of a Holley four-barrel carburetor, Edelbrock Performer intake, MSD ignition, and Hedman headers that add more power as they also contribute to the rumble of the dual exhaust.  Out on the road you're going to feel plenty of power, but there's comfort, too.  The power steering, three-speed automatic transmission, and modern tires all contribute to an overall easy cruising feeling in this muscle machine.

This is the vintage Dodge that does it all.  It has a great appearance inside and out; it has a powerful V8 under the hood; and it's available right now at a great price.  So you know this is a great deal that won't stick around here for long.  Call today!!!
title: 1965 Dodge Coronet

description: Great Lakes Classic Cars
Proudly presents
1974 Cadillac Coupe DeVille
This attractive Promendade Gold Metallic Cadillac, accented by the Dark Brown vinyl top and unique Gold Maharajah Cloth with Leather interior, is certain to add character to any trip.
In the 1974 Cadillac Coupe DeVille, the glove box was replaced with a lockable storage compartment under the dashboard. The option was unpopular and was discontinued after the 1976 model year.
This year also saw the optional introduction of air bags.
From the 1974 Cadillac brochure:
"A quiet sensation... The Coupe deVille.

There is first the styling. New. Elegant. Young. Its beautiful new lines, highlighted by the private quarter window, further accent its youthful flavor. As does the new grille design. There's finer engine performance... from start to stop. Then there is the quiet. As do all '74 Cadillacs, the Coupe

DeVille features a new level of quiet- both inside and out. Even less engine noise with high-damping engine mounts, a fan clutch and a muffler for air intake. Inside the car, an acoustical network of sound-deadening materials- including double seals on doors- further reduces road vibrations and the amount of traffic noise entering the passenger compartment...."
What a ride this Caddy is!  Plenty of power and plenty of comfort.
Feel free to contact us with any questions on this Beautiful Boulevard Cruiser!
